  <prompt>Edit `NarrativeBullet.tsx`. Replace inline 5-icon row with Fluent v9 `Menu` / `MenuTrigger` (`MoreHorizontalRegular` icon) / `MenuList` / `MenuItem`. Inline: regarding-name link + optionally 1 quick action (default: none). Overflow menu items in order: Mark as read, Remove from briefing, Keep on briefing for 7 more days, Add to To Do, Dismiss, Open record. Match semantic-search PCF list visual pattern. Touch targets meet WCAG.</prompt>
  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. Expert in Fluent UI v9 + React hooks + Xrm.WebApi.</role>
  <goal>NarrativeBullet shows: (inline) regarding-name link; (overflow `⋯` button) Fluent v9 Menu with 6 actions in defined order. No inline 5-icon row. Keyboard navigation works; screen reader announces menu role; touch targets ≥44×44px per WCAG.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>FR-18: R3 UAT defect — inline 5-icon row collides visually and confuses users. Three-dot overflow menu (semantic-search PCF list pattern) is the redesign. R3's 3 actions (Check/Remove/Keep) move into the menu unchanged; add To Do (R2 ADR-024) preserved; Dismiss + Open record are new.</background>
