  <steps>
    <step order="1">Inspect existing NarrativeBullet.tsx; document current inline 5-icon row structure + callback prop names</step>
    <step order="2">Inspect semantic-search PCF list visual pattern for reference styling</step>
    <step order="3">Add Fluent v9 imports: `Menu`, `MenuTrigger`, `MenuButton` (or icon-only Button), `MenuList`, `MenuItem`, `MenuPopover`, `MoreHorizontalRegular`</step>
    <step order="4">Define `NarrativeBulletAction` type with action ids: 'markAsRead', 'remove', 'keep', 'addToDo', 'dismiss', 'openRecord'</step>
    <step order="5">Replace inline 5-icon row with: regarding-name link (left) + overflow Menu (right)</step>
    <step order="6">Build MenuList with 6 MenuItems in defined order; each MenuItem has icon + label + onClick handler that calls a single `onAction(actionId)` prop</step>
    <step order="7">Ensure touch targets ≥44×44px (Fluent v9 default sizes; verify with size='medium' on MenuButton)</step>
    <step order="8">Apply semantic tokens only (no raw hex) for any custom styling; verify dark mode renders correctly</step>
    <step order="9">Update component prop types: replace per-action callbacks with single `onAction(actionId: NarrativeBulletAction)` to keep wire-up clean</step>
    <step order="10">Add `aria-label` to overflow button ("More actions"); ensure MenuList items are keyboard-navigable</step>
    <step order="11">Add Jest tests: menu opens on click; menu opens via keyboard (Tab + Enter); each of 6 items present in order; Esc closes; clicking item fires onAction with correct id</step>
    <step order="12">Run `npm test`; verify all pass</step>
    <step order="13">Run `npm run build` to verify TypeScript compiles</step>
    <step order="14">Run `/conflict-check` against R3 PR #451 (NarrativeBullet.tsx is high-risk overlap)</step>
    <step order="15">Update TASK-INDEX.md ✅</step>
